  "couplingIntensity": "None",
  "description": "Two figure-8 loops collide at their crossing point — the feedback at that juncture is high enough to create audible interference. Diffusion is deliberately low so the collision is legible: you hear the echoes intersecting. The modulation desyncs the loops over time, so no two bars sound identical. Pure flux.",
